The actress Rita Wilson announced on Tuesday that she was diagnosed with breast cancer . 
  She underwent a double mastectomy and reconstructive surgery last week and is expected to make a full recovery . 
  The 58-year-old actress tweeted that she is 'overwhelmed with gratitude' for her supporters . 
  On Tuesday, she revealed that her first test for the disease was negative but she was correctly diagnosed after seeking a second opinion . 
  She is married to actor Tom Hanks . 
 